    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty grim outlook. i mean, i get the cost thing, but what about the other side? some people say if workers have more cash they'll spend more in the local community which might actually help businesses in the long run. is that even a real possibility or is it just wishful thinking?",
