    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "really? so you think the whole idea of boosting local purchasing power to help the economy is just a myth? sounds a bit extreme to say it's just something people use to hike taxes. what about the argument that it helps reduce poverty and creates a more stable workforce? isn't there any merit to that side of the debate?",
